==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lithium
<hw>Lith"i*um</hw> <pr>(l⟦icr⟧th"⟦icr⟧*⟦ucr⟧m)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[NL., from Gr. <grk>li`qeios</grk> of stone, fr. <grk>li`qos</grk>
stone.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A metallic element of the alkaline
group, occurring in several minerals, as petalite, spodumene,
lepidolite, triphylite, etc., and otherwise widely disseminated, though
in small quantities.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ When isolated it is a soft, silver white metal,
tarnishing and oxidizing very rapidly in the air. It is the lightest
solid element known, specific gravity being 0.59. Symbol Li. Atomic
weight 7.0 So called from having been discovered in a
mineral.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Litho</ent>⟦br⟧
